result.execSummary:
The defendant Tracy Lynn Gehrke #984000 was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Schedule I, II Narcotics [Modifiers: Possession with Intent to Deliver/Distribute a Controlled Substance On or Near a School], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tracy Lynn Gehrke in court with attorney Sam Joseph Filippo.  Frederick j Schellgell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA calls case at 2:04 p.m.  Cites appearances.  Resolution reached.  DA Schellgell states agreement.  Def will plead NC to 16CF54 and 16CF33, 18 mos P/18 mos ES, waive costs, DNA on record so no further sample, during ES, no possession of illegal drugs and prescriptions only in amount prescribed and prescribed only for her.  Sentence to be concurrent on both cases and with MI sentence.   Atty Filippo agrees with DA Schellgell's recitation of agreement.  Def pleads NC to sole counts in 16CF54 and 16CF33.  Court  questions def re plea-finds freely and voluntarily pleads.  PLQ filed.  Court inserts #s.  Reviewed by court.  Court addresses def atty re PLQ.  Def admits signing.  No coercion, voluntarily signed and understands rights giving up.  Atty Filippo satisfied def freely pleads.  Court accepts plea and finds guilty.  Following agreement and sentences def to 18 months Prison followed by 18 months Extended Supervision, concurrent on both cases and with MI sentence defendant is currently serving.  If MI sentence is completed before WI case is completed, DA Schellgell will address at that time.  Not intention of DA that if MI sentence is done early, WI sentence is done.  May consider prison time being converted to extended supervision if only a couple of weeks, but to be addressed.  Court deems def eligible for any programs now available or that become available to her.  Court deems def eligible for CIP and Substance Abuse Program.  Condition during ES for def is no possession of illegal drugs and prescriptions only in amount prescribed and prescribed only for her.  Court completes WEDS and copy is provided to def.  Adj. 2:19 p.m.  klr
